# pwn.college Assembly Assortment Cheat Sheet

## Function Template

```asm
.intel_syntax noprefix
.global solve

solve:
    ; code
    ret
```

### Calling Convention

| Purpose      | Register |
| ------------ | -------- |
| 1st argument | rdi      |
| 2nd argument | rsi      |
| Return value | rax      |

---

# Bitwise Operations

## AND (`&`)

Keeps bits where mask has 1s.

```asm
and rax, MASK
```

Examples:

```asm
and rax, 1
```

Keep lowest bit.

```asm
and rax, 0xff
```

Keep lowest byte.

```asm
and rax, 0xffff
```

Keep lowest 16 bits.

### Mental Rule

```text
AND = KEEP
```

---

## OR (`|`)

Turns bits on.

```asm
or rax, MASK
```

Example:

```asm
or rax, 0x20
```

Set ASCII case bit.

### Mental Rule

```text
OR = SET
```

---

## XOR (`^`)

Flips bits.

```asm
xor rax, MASK
```

Examples:

```asm
xor rax, 1
```

Swap 0 and 1.

```asm
xor al, 0x20
```

Toggle ASCII case.

### Mental Rule

```text
XOR = TOGGLE
```

---

# ASCII Case Tricks

## Uppercase → Lowercase

```asm
or al, 0x20
```

Example:

```text
A -> a
P -> p
```

---

## Lowercase → Uppercase

```asm
and al, 0xdf
```

Example:

```text
a -> A
p -> P
```

---

## Toggle Case

```asm
xor al, 0x20
```

Example:

```text
A -> a
a -> A
```

---

# String Loops

## Uppercase String

```asm
loop:
    mov al, [rdi]
    cmp al, 0
    je done

    and al, 0xdf
    mov [rdi], al

    inc rdi
    jmp loop

done:
    ret
```

---

## Lowercase String

```asm
loop:
    mov al, [rdi]
    cmp al, 0
    je done

    or al, 0x20
    mov [rdi], al

    inc rdi
    jmp loop

done:
    ret
```

---

## Swap Case String

```asm
loop:
    mov al, [rdi]
    cmp al, 0
    je done

    xor al, 0x20
    mov [rdi], al

    inc rdi
    jmp loop

done:
    ret
```

